### Installing from PyPI

Simply install with:
```bash
python3 -m pip install {{ python_package_distribution_name }}
```

If you are on jupyter, and don't have the rights to install packages system-wide, then you can install with:
```python
! pip install --user {{ python_package_distribution_name }}
